
⸻

FG-351 — OA Screen-Share Protocol (If Allowed, 90 Seconds Max)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: A brief, policy-clean screen-share lands the pin faster than words.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Check policy; label “Demonstrative A” (neutral); show one page (anchor); add callouts (region/pin); stop in ≤90s; file a same-day notice with the view-copy and hash.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 5-line screen-share script (page, region, pin, ask, stop).
	•	✅ Model Response: “Showing Dkt 18 at 2—‘did not reach harm’ (highlight). Relief: remand 21d for findings. (View copy SHA-256 …).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: One page shared > ten pages described.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A monitor with one page, a yellow callout box, and a tiny hash tag.

⸻

FG-352 — Live Note-Taker Role (Pins • Questions • Time)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: One teammate logs pins and time so the close targets what’s hot.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Columns: Judge • Topic • Quote/pin • Minutes; tag “close with X”; hand the card to counsel at T-1:00.
	•	📝 Assignment: Print a 6-row OA note sheet and assign a note-taker.
	•	✅ Model Response: “J2: 6m on ‘not reached’ (Dkt 18:2); close with 21-day findings block.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: The best close is chosen, not improvised.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A clipboard with a heat bar beside one row.

⸻

FG-353 — One-Page Case Snapshot (Posture • Pins • Ask)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: A single page can replace five emails.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Three blocks: Posture triangle (statute/clock/copies), Two pins (anchor/gap), Two-line order (primary/fallback). Hash; date; share publicly.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build your snapshot for the current matter and save as PDF.
	•	✅ Model Response: “§1292; Rule 58 08/15 → NOA 08/19; gap Dkt 18:2; Relief: remand 21d (a–d).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: A map, not a memo.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A one-page card with a triangle, two pin dots, and an order strip.

⸻

FG-354 — Affidavit Template Kit (Identity • Timeline • Proof)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Keep a sworn template so evidence ships in minutes, not days.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Sections: Identity; 10 bullets with dates/times; Exhibit pins (A-1/B-1); Perjury line; Signature/date; export as fillable.
	•	📝 Assignment: Create a 1-page fillable affidavit with three exhibit placeholders.
	•	✅ Model Response: “07/31 09:42 USPS receipt (Ex A-1); 08/02 16:10 error 503 (Ex B-1). I declare under penalty of perjury….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: The right form turns facts into proof.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A sworn stamp over a bullet timeline sheet.

⸻

FG-355 — Findings Gap Heatmap (Where the Order Stopped)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Visualize which factors the court did not reach.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: 2×2 grid (Success/Harm/Equities/Public); mark reached/not reached; pin the gap line; attach a 21-day instruction.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 4-cell heatmap with one pin per cell; add to OA packet.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Harm—Not reached (Dkt 18 at 2) → remand 21d for findings (a–d).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Seeing the hole invites a patch.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Four cells; one greyed “Not reached” with a red circle.

⸻

FG-356 — Order Comparison Table (Before → After Line)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Show the fix in one table, not a page.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Table: Page:Line • Before • After • Reason • Pin; attach corrected page; no schedule change line; new SHA-256.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 5-row comparison table for one order.
	•	✅ Model Response: “p.12 n.3 ‘reached harm’ → ‘did not reach’; reason: transcription; Dkt 18:2; new SHA-256 ….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Editors sign what they can see.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A before/after strip with a small pencil icon.

⸻

FG-357 — Return-to-Panel Status Clock (After Mandate)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Post-mandate, run a dated checklist to closure.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Card: Task • Owner • Due • Proof pin (findings/notice/calendar); set status date; hash the status PDF; file every 10–14 days until done.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 5-row return clock for the remand window.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Findings by 09/15 — Dkt 101:2–3; status 09/22; OA window Tue/Wed 2–4 PM.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Discipline makes mandates real.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A mini dashboard with one yellow “due soon.”

⸻

FG-358 — Stipulated Record Corrections (Neutral, Task-Only)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Fix record hygiene by stipulation, not motion practice.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Identify missing/mis-indexed pages; attach certified copies; no argument change; propose task-only order; list new hash; pin-sub table only if pages move.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line joint notice with a 6-row correction list.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Add Tab 5 (Dkt 88:6); correct AR 204 date; no merits change; SHA-256 …; order attached.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Neutral fixes get instant yes.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A tidy checklist with two signatures below.

⸻

FG-359 — Accessibility Appendix (Alt-Text • Reading Order • Tags)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: An accessible appendix reads as professional and persuasive.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Alt-text on figures (“hatched band = timing gap”); verify reading order; tag H2/H3 to mirror bookmarks; hash file; note PDF/UA if supported.
	•	📝 Assignment: Add alt-text to two figures; export with PDF/UA and a hash footer.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Appx Vol. 1 PDF/UA; alt-text on Tabs D-2/D-3; SHA-256 ….”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Access and persuasion rise together.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A PDF tile with “Alt-text ✓ / Order ✓ / Tags ✓”.

⸻

FG-360 — Public Release Bundle (ZIP Layout You’ll Reuse)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Publish a repeatable bundle: docs first, hashes included.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: ZIP root: StartHere.md • OA_Card.pdf • Findings_Grid.pdf • Relief_Bank.md • Appendix_Guide.pdf • CHECKSUMS.txt; filenames dated; README with links + hashes; mirror link with same hash.
	•	📝 Assignment: Export a v-tagged release ZIP with a CHECKSUMS.txt and README.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Release v6 — kit ZIP posted; SHA-256 …; mirrors M-1/M-2 same hash.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Packaging multiplies impact.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A ribboned ZIP tile with a fingerprint tag and a small README card.